In order for you to work on this section easily you will need the following
VS code
DBeaver
Postgress Extension on vs code

How to set it up
Install the extension:
Open the Extensions view in VS Code (Ctrl+Shift+X or Cmd+Shift+X).
Search for "PostgreSQL" in the marketplace.
Select the official extension authored by Microsoft (it has a blue elephant icon) and click Install.
Connect to your database:
After installation, a PostgreSQL icon (elephant) will appear in your Activity Bar on the sidebar; click it.
In the PostgreSQL explorer pane, select Add Connection.
Enter your connection details, such as the host address (e.g., localhost for a local database), port (default is 5432), username, and password when prompted.
You can also choose to connect via a connection string or browse Azure-hosted databases if applicable.
Select Test Connection to verify your details, then Connect to establish the connection.